---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Sena Lim | Case Studies">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 space-y-12">

    <section class="space-y-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">Inclusion & Everyday Systems</h1>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <!-- Youth Mental Health -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/bluesg.webp" alt="Youth Mental Health" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Youth Mental Health</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            For youth mental health, I imagined an emotional check-in tool for schools, 
            helping spot distress early and making support feel normal and approachable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Ageing with Dignity  -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/yara.webp" alt="Ageing with Dignity" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Ageing with Dignity</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            For seniors and caregivers, I mapped out simple concepts that could make support
routines less stressful—maybe a tap-in mood kiosk, or delivery rhythms that help staff 
and users avoid burnout.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Inclusive Digitalisation -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/neuron.webp" alt="Inclusive Digitalisation" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Inclusive Digitalisation</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            For digital inclusion, I explored what it might take to move beyond pilot programs, 
building lasting digital partnerships where everyone’s voice is included from day one.
          </p>
        </div>

 <!-- Systems for People of Determination -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/neuron.webp" alt="Systems for People of Determination" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Systems for People of Determination/h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            I sketched out how support for people with disabilities could be rolled out step by step, 
with a focus on daily realities instead of frameworks.
          </p>
        </div>

 <!-- Building Everyday Trust (CDC Vouchers) -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/neuron.webp" alt="Building Everyday Trust (CDC Vouchers)" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Building Everyday Trust (CDC Vouchers)</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Even for something like national vouchers, I looked at how thoughtful design can help hesitant users 
trust and adopt new tools, not just feel left behind (This thinking builds on my reflection here)
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

<section class="space-y-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center">Mission-Critical Strategy</h1>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <!-- Crisis Triage System -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/bluesg.webp" alt="Crisis Triage System" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Crisis Triage System</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            I mapped out a unified triage and tasking system for military teams, aiming to 
balance human judgment with tech support and fit real decision-making workflows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Public Safety Triage Ecosystem -->
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition space-y-2">
          <img src="/images/yara.webp" alt="Public Safety Triage Ecosystem" class="rounded mb-4" />
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg">Public Safety Triage Ecosystem</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            I also explored what an AI-powered triage process for public safety might look like, 
focusing on explainability and compliance so that technology earns trust, not confusion.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
